### 🔴 Issue 3: Progress bar color is hardcoded red instead of using `themeColor`
**Where:** `EditorPage.tsx` lines 213 and 283

**Current code:**
```tsx
className="h-full bg-[#b91c1c] rounded-full transition-all duration-700 ease-out"
```

**Problem:** The theme color is dynamic (users can change it in the Design panel). But the progress bar always stays hardcoded red. This is inconsistent.

**Fix instruction:**
```tsx
// Change both instances (desktop + mobile sidebar) to:
style={{ 
  width: `${(Object.values(getSectionStatus(resumeData)).filter(Boolean).length / 13) * 100}%`,
  backgroundColor: themeColor
}}
className="h-full rounded-full transition-all duration-700 ease-out"
```
> Note: `themeColor` is already available in the `ctx` object, just make sure it is destructured in `EditorPage.tsx`.

