### 🟡 Issue 5: Sidebar header has no dynamic subtitle
**What was asked:** A subtitle that tells users how many sections remain.

**What was built:** Just the count "11/13" in mono font — no human-readable context text.

**Fix instruction:** Below the `h2` title, add:
```tsx
const completedCount = Object.values(getSectionStatus(resumeData)).filter(Boolean).length
// Then in JSX:
<p className="text-[11px] text-zinc-500 mt-0.5">
  {completedCount === 13
    ? 'All sections complete ✓'
    : `${13 - completedCount} section${13 - completedCount !== 1 ? 's' : ''} remaining`}
</p>
```
> Add this to BOTH the desktop and mobile sidebar headers.

